<subSubSection id="3ABC5151F962F2166409418EEBD27872" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="398F198482C625CABC5E5D3B656FC760" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0BE679C1C76AA334811128EA37130D40" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="13" pageNumber="46">
<bibRefCitation id="75D7AE92E30606430E991BE658E41E4F" author="Seguy, E" journalOrPublisher="Memorias e estudos do Museu Zoologico da Universidade de Coimbra" pageId="26" pageNumber="59" pagination="5 - 80" title="Contributions a l'etude de la faune du Mozambique. Voyage de M. P. Lesne (1928 - 1929)." volume="67" year="1933">
<normalizedToken id="928C1E1DF426343AC3AAED4E7E240822" originalValue="Séguy">Seguy</normalizedToken>
(1933)
</bibRefCitation>
described a species of the vittiger group from 
<normalizedToken id="8C4A84928EC4E9D9F05DC47D8BD3A0D2" originalValue="Côte">Cote</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="042AE2C839C6043E37103666A444F123" originalValue="d’Ivoire">d'Ivoire</normalizedToken>
, which has differentiated F1 composite spines; i.e. the spines are borne on protruding tubercules that decrease in size distally. He called the species 
<taxonomicName id="DDFF1A6236A53E59E73D7D8566FB4D80" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus ornatus" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">Zaprionus ornatus</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="55ECFF724896DFCB3DDA1A018F513D8D" author="Collart, A" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Musee Royale d'Histoire Naturelle de Belgique" pageId="25" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 15" title="Les Zaprionus du Congo belge (Diptera: Drosophilidae)." volume="13" year="1937 a">Collart (1937a)</bibRefCitation>
considered this character an intraspecific variation and synonymised 
<taxonomicName id="D885E2E3C5921BBB01202EF413624ED7" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus ornatus" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">Zaprionus ornatus</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="235A05D458159B426C3F9C5BB27B8719" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus vittiger" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittiger">Zaprionus vittiger</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="CFEFA1934AEFBAEC6209A73491CA0FF2" author="Chassagnard, MT" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="25" pageNumber="58" pagination="173 - 194" title="Le sous-genre Zaprionus s. str. Definition de groupes d'especes et revision du sous-groupe vittiger (Diptera: Drosophilidae)." volume="29" year="1993">Chassagnard and Tsacas (1993)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed 
<normalizedToken id="9EB94AF4FB89BD6803444B04839F74EE" originalValue="Séguy’s">Seguy's</normalizedToken>
female holotype and illustrated the distinctive elongated spermatheca that had also been previously illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="91FAD3E42C05E38F1791DAAB7713A945" author="Burla, H" journalOrPublisher="Revue Suisse de Zoologie" pageId="25" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 218" title="Zur Kenntnis der Drosophiliden der Elfenbeinkuste (Franzosisch West-Afrika)." volume="61" year="1954">Burla (1954)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="BF94685AE444FD70D32BD4E16B27AC62" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus aff subsp. vittiger" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="aff" subSpecies="vittiger">Zaprionus aff. vittiger</taxonomicName>
. In the same paper, they also described a new species from Congo with the distinctive elongated spermatheca and F1 ornamentation. They called the new species 
<taxonomicName id="885DEBC6F9D33ABCC4F60C4319047D14" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus megalorchis" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalorchis">Zaprionus megalorchis</taxonomicName>
and noted that the only difference between it and 
<taxonomicName id="8097B6B7F16AB65A3DC7DA747EAD8574" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus ornatus" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">Zaprionus ornatus</taxonomicName>
was the presence of silver pilosity on the inner side of flagellomere I in 
<taxonomicName id="6533DC1103E8A40CC99559CFC4B91995" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus ornatus" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">Zaprionus ornatus</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="3DD228B79D180EE6F254E27A5194E00A" author="Yassin, A" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="26" pageNumber="59" pagination="903 - 915" title="Grafting the molecular phylogenetic tree with morphological branches to reconstruct the evolutionary history of the genus Zaprionus (Diptera: Drosophilidae)." volume="47" year="2008 a">Yassin et al. (2008a)</bibRefCitation>
erected the megalorchis species complex for the two species. However, 
<pageBreakToken id="41B9A14758AD6319B043340E6D6D9C36" pageId="14" pageNumber="47" start="start">we</pageBreakToken>
have examined a number of strains collected from the type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="24BD2AF0726D4011CCAF98D20BE77779" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus megalorchis" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalorchis">Zaprionus megalorchis</taxonomicName>
and found the flagellomere I pilosity to be polymorphic. We consider thus 
<taxonomicName id="B11E4C51DE964FEABC2C8F8A906F2627" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus megalorchis" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalorchis">Zaprionus megalorchis</taxonomicName>
Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, syn. n. and 
<taxonomicName id="D35A337A7F762134B53FC8E0A24E855E" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus aff subsp. vittiger" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="aff" subSpecies="vittiger">Zaprionus aff. vittiger</taxonomicName>
Burla, syn. n. to be junior synonyms to 
<taxonomicName id="7CF16DF52D304011087E8555656E8EAB" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus ornatus" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">Zaprionus ornatus</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="500185FB89B6F70E17ACF375D32DBC18" originalValue="Séguy">Seguy</normalizedToken>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="0320FFEB84BE0BA0FF22A0D0ACD4BE7E" author="Yassin, A" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Ecology Resources" pageId="26" pageNumber="59" pagination="491 - 501" title="DNA barcode discovers two cryptic species and two geographical radiations in the invasive drosophilid Zaprionus indianus." volume="8" year="2008 b">Yassin et al. (2008b)</bibRefCitation>
have also considered 
<taxonomicName id="DE8BC756B32404C2C510D8BFFBC74A7B" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus megalorchis" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalorchis">Zaprionus megalorchis</taxonomicName>
(and thus 
<taxonomicName id="F0E2584FB1D39332235519C86AB5C49A" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus ornatus" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatus">Zaprionus ornatus</taxonomicName>
) a member of the indianus species complex, but it is considered here as belonging to an independent, monophyletic complex along with 
<taxonomicName id="B575BF69A9487DEE1011E213C4C60819" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Zaprionus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zaprionus litos" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="litos">Zaprionus litos</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="01BDD7246ED493F658E0052673268D4B" pageId="14" pageNumber="47">Yassin et al., in press</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="3AD81D7252A4425EECAD5E530AFB812E" pageId="14" pageNumber="47">
